pen";s:5:"title";s:55:"What Are The Open And Close Limit On Garage Door Opener";s:3:"alt";s:19:"veteran garage door";s:3:"url";s:85:"https://veterangaragedoor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/loose-garage-door-cable.jpeg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSdNPMgP3fZRusWw2KbiME_i707sDVlU7KS2Q";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:2448;s:6:"height";i:3264;s:6:"source";s:93:"https://veterangaragedoor.com/faq/what-are-the-open-and-close-limits-of-a-garage-door-opener/";s:6:"domain";s:21:"veterangaragedoor.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:59:{i:0;s:138:"If your garage door cables are loose it could be as simple as securing the torsion tube and torsion springs and then rewinding the cables.";i:1;s:112:"This simple for a garage door technician but is very dangerous if you do not have the proper tools and training.";i:2;s:24:"Loose cables could be a.";i:3;s:114:"Cable on right side of garage door is slack when door closed and coils around end of spring crookedly when opened.";i:4;s:62:"I just had to adjust the lifting tension for the door to open.";i:5;s:182:"Cables attach at the bottom brackets on the bottom corners of door and run up or up and back to the springs When springs are under load the spring pulls cables to assist lifting the.";i:6;s:66:"This opens the door easily for opener or opening manually by hand.";i:7;s:35:"Cables may loose tension over time.";i:8;s:151:"When cables loose tension they will sag and this is most common with extension springs Extension springs are found on sides of door or run along sides.";i:9;s:54:"Garage Door cable came off on one side of garage door.";i:10;s:35:"Now the garage door will not close.";i:11;s:42:"The door comes down half way and is stuck.";i:12;s:87:"I had shut the door and it hit something and then the cable got messed up and came off.";i:13;s:127:"When a garage door starts to sag to one side instead of at the center it is usually not from warping that can happen over time.";i:14;s:51:"Instead there are two problem areas to investigate.";i:15;s:43:"The first is the hinges on the door itself.";i:16;s:65:"Over time the hinges on one side of the door can start to loosen.";i:17;s:188:"If your cables are tightly wound on the pulley but 1 side of the door is uneven then you need to adjust the tension on the torsion spring mounted above the center of the garage door frame.";i:18;s:23:"Step 1 - Push the Door.";i:19;s:71:"Push the door back to adjust the door and get the center-aligned again.";i:20;s:125:"It is possible that the vertical track down the side has gone out of alignment and shifted due to a slightly loose lag screw.";i:21;s:90:"By pushing the door back into position you should have made the vertical track straighten.";i:22;s:35:"Step 2 - Check that it is Straight.";i:23;s:59:"The door might be hard to open and close due to it binding.";i:24;s:72:"There may be a large gap of space between the stop molding and the door.";i:25;s:31:"A crooked or off-balanced door.";i:26;s:88:"Any of these situations indicate that one or both garage door tracks need to be aligned.";i:27;s:122:"Therefore almost any improper use or damage to the drums tracks or garage door can cause garage door cables to come loose.";i:28;s:268:"A few of the most common reasons for garage door cables to come loose include the garage door setting down on an object loose set screws bad roller wheels bent garage door sections excessive force when opening or closing manually broken extension spring and much more.";i:29;s:100:"To fix your garage door cables youll want to release the tension of the springs by lifting the door.";i:30;s:102:"While youre at it disengage the electricity from your garage door opener if you have an automatic one.";i:31;s:89:"You dont want any electrical accidents to happen while youre working on your garage door.";i:32;s:30:"WHAT CAUSES A CABLE DRUM SLIP.";i:33;s:88:"Your garage door opens when the springs apply the right amount of tension to the cables.";i:34;s:65:"Properly functioning cables lift the door and spool on the drums.";i:35;s:32:"Cables can slip off the rollers.";i:36;s:43:"If that happens the cable may appear loose.";i:37;s:47:"Here are a few reasons a cable may malfunction.";i:38;s:155:"If your door has a gap on one side or the other when its closed the problem is most likely due to a break or other issue with one of the extension springs.";i:39;s:88:"Repairing your garage door springs can be a dangerous job due to the weight of the door.";i:40;s:155:"If you suspect you need to adjust one or both of the extension springs on your door or one or both of the springs are broken give us a call here at Whitby.";i:41;s:174:"Garage doors which have become crooked or wonky may be suffering from jumped cables which is when one or both cables have loosened from the cable drums and started to unwind.";i:42;s:137:"Jumped cables can be caused by the door hitting an object during operation or if it has been lifted too fast while being opened manually.";i:43;s:119:"Deterioration and general wear and tear can cause old cables to snap which can affect the alignment of the garage door.";i:44;s:58:"Overhead garage doors utilize two cables one on each side.";i:45;s:121:"But the cables are installed in a slightly different way based on whether the door utilizes torsion or extension springs.";i:46;s:93:"In the case of the former the cables hold the doors weight as the torsion spring balances it.";i:47;s:45:"Check the ends of your new garage door cable.";i:48;s:60:"One end has a tip that fits perfectly inside the cable drum.";i:49;s:61:"Put it inside the drum and wind it tightly on the cable drum.";i:50;s:100:"When youre done fix the other end which is a cable loop to the pin at the bottom of the garage door.";i:51;s:133:"The_fiddler normally a 7 high door will require 75 full turns or 30 14 turns add 1 full turn for each additional foot in door height.";i:52;s:137:"I think the cables are jumping because 4 turns arent enough to keep the drums turning to take up the cable therefore causing clabe slack.";i:53;s:28:"Try 75 turns on each spring.";i:54;s:61:"The garage door needs to be serviced by a trained technician.";i:55;s:203:"This is a very common problem that occurs to panel-lift garage doors and the reason for this is that the cable has come off the drum wheel on one side when the garage door was in the fully open position.";i:56;s:72:"Garage door cables so small yet so integral to the function of the door.";i:57;s:161:"If youre having problems opening or closing your garage door or if you have loose wires hanging down by your garage door you may have a broken garage door cable.";i:58;s:67:"Replacing just the cable is possible but the job isnt for everyone.";}}